apiDescription: This enumeration is the list of the possible error outcomes for the try_send method.

enum variants:
The data could not be sent on the sync_channel because it would require that
the callee block to send the data.
If this is a buffered channel, then the buffer is full at this time. If
this is not a buffered channel, then there is no Receiver available to
acquire the data.

This sync_channel's receiving half has disconnected, so the data could not be
sent. The data is returned back to the callee in this case.

trait implementations.name: impl<T> std::marker::Send for std::sync::mpsc::TrySendError<T> where T: std::marker::Send
impl<T> std::marker::Sync for std::sync::mpsc::TrySendError<T> where T: std::marker::Sync
